quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  27,45,"And indeed, We sent to Thamûd their brother Saleh<i class=""s"">(saying) </i>, “Worship Allah.” But they promptly became two disputing groups."
  27,46,"He said, “O my people, why do you ask that the bad be hastened before the good? If only you would ask Allah’s forgiveness so that you may be shown mercy.”"
  27,47,"They said, “We consider you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>a bad omen, and those with you<i class=""s"">(too) </i>.” He said, “Your omen is with Allah. In fact, you are a people being tried.”"
  27,48,"And there were nine persons in the city who were spreading corruption in the land and would not reform."
  27,49,"They said, “Swear by Allah to one another that <span class=""h"">we<sup foot_note=""80743"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">will surely attack him</span>and his family at night, and then <span class=""h"">we</span><span class=""h"">will emphatically tell</span>his kinsman seeking retribution, ‘We did not witness the murder of his family, and we are indeed truthful.’”"
  27,50,"And they schemed a scheme, and We schemed a scheme while they were unaware."
  27,51,"So look<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>at how the outcome of their scheming <span class=""h"">was that We{1} </span>did destroy them and their people, all of them.",footnotes:1:Nafieʻ, Ibn Kathir, Abu ʻAmr, Ibn ʻAmer and Abu Jaʻfar read it as: “. . . how the outcome of their scheming was: We did destroy them . . .”
  27,52,"So here are their houses, vacant, on account of their injustice. Indeed, in this is surely a sign for people who know."
  27,53,"And We saved those who believed and were mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>."
  27,54,"And Lot<i class=""s"">(too) </i>, when he said to his people, “Do you commit obscenity while you can see<i class=""s"">(its shamefulness) </i>?"
  27,55,"Do you approach men with lust instead of women? Rather you are an ignorant people.”"
